title: Golden Void performs "Rise to the Out of Reach"/"Smiling Raven" - Converse Rubber Tracks: Ready, Set
description:
Bay area heavy rock supergroup Golden Void materialized from Earthless guitarist Isaiah Mitchell's blazingly psychedelic riffs, Assemble Head in Sunburst Sound's Camilla Saufly-Mitchell's looming organ playing, and the heavy-as-hammers rhythm section of Aaron Morgan and Justin Pinkerton, who had been playing together in various bands since high school days. Watch as they take us on a trip through the hay day of San Francisco rock during "Rise to the Out of Reach"/ "Smiling Raven".

For more on Converse Rubber Tracks:
http://www.converse.com/rubbertracks

On June 28th Converse will open it's San Francisco store on 838 Market St. Be sure to check it out!
